                android:text="Sauté Aromatics:

In a large pot, heat cooking oil over medium heat. Sauté the minced garlic until golden brown, then add the chopped onions. Cook until the onions are translucent.
Add Pork:

Add the pork cubes and cook until browned on all sides.
Add Liver:

Add the pork liver and cook for a few minutes until it changes color.
Add Soy Sauce and Tomatoes:

Pour in the soy sauce and add the chopped tomatoes. Cook until the tomatoes are soft.
Pour Tomato Sauce and Broth:

Add the tomato sauce and pork broth (or water) to the pot. Stir well to combine.
Simmer:

Drop in the bay leaves and bring the mixture to a simmer. Cover the pot and let it cook for about 30 minutes or until the pork is tender.
Add Vegetables:

Add the diced potatoes and carrots. Simmer until the vegetables are almost tender.
Add Bell Pepper and Peas:

Add the diced bell pepper and green peas. Simmer for an additional 5-7 minutes or until all the vegetables are tender.
Season:

Season the menudo with salt and pepper to taste. Adjust the seasoning as needed.
Serve:

Remove the bay leaves and serve the Pork Menudo hot, ideally with steamed rice."
